(104, 'Hippocastanaceae', 'Horsechestnut', 'Aesculus', NULL, NULL, 'parviflora', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'shrub', 'deciduous', 'mounding', 'full sun or light shade', 'regular watering', NULL, 'Yes', 'summer', 'Yes', NULL, 'summer flowers, autumn foliage color', NULL, '8', '8', '15-20', '10-12', '5', '9', 'Aesculus parviflora is a large deciduous, densely mounded, suckering multi-stemmed shrub. Pruning is usually not necessary but smaller size could be maintained as A. parviflora will take a heavy rejuvenation pruning. ', 'Aesculus parviflora grows best in a rich well-drained soil in full sun to light shade. The bottlebrush buckeye does not tolerate dry soils and grows best with regular watering during dry weather. Pruning is usually not necessary, but ample space should be provided for this suckering shrub to fully develop. There are no disease or pest problems of any significance.', 'Bottlebrush buckeye is a shrubby relative of the tough horse chestnut. This medium to large multi-stemmed bush is dotted with 12 inch long spidery white flower spikes in mid-summer. In early spring the new leaves emerge a lovely salmon pink that turns to a deep rich green for the growing season. ', 'Try underplanting it with the bright green grass of Hakonechloa macra.', NULL, NULL, 'Committee', '2008', 'Shrubs - Vines', NULL, NULL, 'Plant Finder 2006-2007 A-Z', 'GPP', 'no', NULL, '2008', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
