(118, 'Amaryllidaceae', NULL, 'Allium', NULL, NULL, 'cristophii', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'bulb', 'deciduous', 'upright', 'full sun', 'drought tolerant', NULL, 'Yes', 'spring', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, NULL, '.5-1.5', '1-2', '2', '2', '5', '8', 'Plants form dense, slowly-spreading clumps over time. Flower stalks reach 2 to 3 feet in height. ', 'Ornamental onions grow best in full sun and sandy soil. It will tolerate clay soils if the location is sloped and water does not puddle in the winter. Leaves will grow through the late winter and spring, only dying back as the bulb begins to flower. Yellowing leaves can be trimmed to the ground or hidden amongst other plants. Bulbs can be planted in the fall.', 'Allium cristophii was selected for its large starburst-like purple flowers that fade to a tawny silver as they dry. The dried seed heads hold up well in the summer garden adding an interesting structural element to later blooming perennials. These bulbs do well in sandy soils and dry locations and are completely drought tolerant. ', 'For dramatic impact, use dark foliage plants such as purple leaved barberries (Berberis thunbergii ''Rosy Glow'') as a backdrop. ', NULL, NULL, 'Forkner', '2002', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, NULL, '2002', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
(119, NULL, NULL, 'Allium', NULL, NULL, 'hollandicum', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Purple Sensation', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'bulb', 'deciduous', NULL, 'full sun', 'drought tolerant', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '3', NULL, NULL, '4', '8', 'Allium hollandicum ''Purple Sensation'' is an upright, bulbous, deciduous perennial with strap-shaped green leaves that reach 12 to 24 inches. The flower stalks reach 30 to 36 inches in height with a flower head that is 4 inches across. ', 'Ornamental onions grow best in full sun and sandy soil. They will tolerate a heavier soil as long as it is very well-drained or even clay soils if the location is sloped and water does not puddle in the winter. Leaves will grow through the late winter and spring, only dying back as the bulb begins to flower. Yellowing leaves can be trimmed to the ground or hidden amongst other plants. Bulbs can be planted in the fall.', 'The brilliant flowers of Allium hollandicum ‘Purple Sensation’ are truly an intense, yet bright, shade of magenta-purple. The four-inch flower heads are held high on stems up to three feet tall and dance above the surrounding plants.  They are great for sandy soils and hot dry locations. This tough bulb is completely drought tolerant.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Newton', '2007', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, 'nominated as Allium aflatunense ''Purple Sensation'' which is not a correct name', 'GPP', NULL, '10/07 added to 2010 as part of collection.', '2010', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
(121, NULL, NULL, 'Allium', NULL, NULL, 'karataviense', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivory Queen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'bulb', 'deciduous', NULL, 'full sun', 'drought tolerant', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '.5', '.75', NULL, NULL, '4', '8', 'This deciduous bulb grows to about 8 to 10 inches tall with two broad arching leaves. It is a beautiful and bold texture to use among late sprouting perennials. ', 'Ornamental onions grow best in full sun and sandy soil. They will tolerate a heavier soil as long as it is very well-drained or even clay soils if the location is sloped and water does not puddle in the winter. Leaves will grow through the late winter and spring, only dying back as the bulb begins to flower. Yellowing leaves can be trimmed to the ground or hidden amongst other plants. Bulbs can be planted in the fall.', 'This short, squat perennial bulb looks great from the moment it emerges in late winter until it dies down in summer. It is one of the few ornamental onions with beautiful foliage. Two fabulous soft gray blue-green broad leaves give an early show. Then in early spring a short flower stalk emerges and opens to a perfect globe of white stars. Once the flowers finish the faded seed heads look like small sunbursts on dried stems. This drought tolerant bulb is excellent for hot dry sites and loves to bake during the summer months.  ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Newton', '2007', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, '10/07 added to 2010 as part of collection.', '2010', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
