(175, NULL, NULL, 'Artemisia', NULL, NULL, 'versicolor', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sea Foam', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'perennial', 'evergreen', NULL, 'full sun', 'drought tolerant when established', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '1.5', NULL, NULL, '4', '9', 'Artemisia versicolor ''Sea Foam'' is a mounding evergreen perennial that grows 12 to 18 inches tall with a spread of 18 to 24 inches. It gets spikes of insignificant, yellow flowers mid-summer which should be removed after blooming.', 'Grow this soft silvery mugwort in full sun for tight compact growth. It requires well drained soil, will tolerate poor sandy or rocky conditions, and is drought tolerant after being established.  The flowers are not significant and can be sheared off to maintain a tidier appearance and give a more compact habit. ', 'Artemisia versicolor ‘Sea Foam’ is a low growing, mound with thread-like curlicues of silver white foliage. This very drought tolerant perennial is great for the front of hot dry beds and for well drained soils. Its sea foam-like leaves add an interesting texture to the garden and would be great tucked into a rockery. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Horn, McLauchlan', '2006', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, 'internet uses both Sea Foam and Seafoam, altho Denver BG lists as Sea Foam', 'GPP', NULL, '03/09 picked for 2011', '2011', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
