(277, NULL, NULL, 'Campanula', NULL, NULL, 'poscharskyana', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'perennial', 'evergreen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', '0.4', '3', '9', 'Serbian bellflower is a prostrate, vigorous, evergreen perennial with underground runners. The small compact foliage is covered with lavender-blue flowers from late spring to mid-summer. It grows to about 4 inches tall and 4 feet wide.   ', 'This evergreen perennial grows well in full sun to light or open shade. It prefers a rich moist or well-drained soil. Provide regular watering during the summer. After flowering, gently shear off the old flower stalks and up to one-third of the plant to keep it looking its best throughout the growing season. ', 'This very vigorous species is great for a brilliant flowering groundcover.  Long lasting, bell shaped, lavender-blue flowers are borne in abundance from late spring to early summer. This spreading perennial will fill in cracks and crevices and is wonderful as a filler for rockeries. It is one of the toughest and best of the low blue flowered campanulas. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Committee', '2007', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, 'groundcover sm. collection', '2009', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL);
