(278, NULL, NULL, 'Campanula', NULL, NULL, 'rotundifolia', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'perennial', 'evergreen', 'spreading', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.5', '0.5', '5', '8', 'Campanula rotundifolia is a vigorous, mounding evergreen perennial. The foliage is only 4 to 6 inches tall and slightly wider, in flower the stems can reach about 12 inches tall.   ', 'This compact small perennial grows well in full sun to light or open shade. It prefers a rich moist or well-drained soil, but will tolerate drought once well established. For longer flowering provide regular watering during the summer. After flowering, gently shear off the old flower stalks to encourage more flowers later in the season.  ', 'A charming native bellflower that is much tougher than its delicate looks suggest. Thin flower stems rise in late spring from a tight mound of small evergreen foliage. Dark blue to lavender-blue bells nod gracefully from these airy stems which dance in a breeze. This is an excellent choice for tucking into crevices in rockeries or using in containers. The small stature of this perennial is great for the edge of the border. Flowering is improved by a hard trim of the faded blooms in early to mid summer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Committee', '2007', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, 'native', '2009', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
(279, NULL, NULL, 'Campanula', NULL, NULL, 'rupestris', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Samantha', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Committee', '2007', 'perennials - bulbs', '', '', '', 'Eliminated', '', '03/09 - eliminated for weakness', '', '', '', 'No', ''),
(280, NULL, NULL, 'Campanula', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Birch Hybrid', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'perennial', 'evergreen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'spring-summer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.5', '4', '7', '"This is one of the smaller campanulas, growing only 4 to 6"" high. Its one-inch-long, bell-shaped flowers are held just above the mat of serrated, kidney-shaped leaves. It spreads by underground runners, but unlike it''s parents C. poscharskyana and C. garganica, not aggressively so. "', 'This evergreen perennial grows well in full sun to light or open shade. It prefers a rich moist or well-drained soil. Provide regular watering during the summer. After flowering, gently shear off the old flower stalks and up to one-third of the plant to keep it looking its best throughout the growing season. ', 'One of the most remarkable characteristics of Campanula ‘Birch Hybrid’ is its ability to steal the garden stage despite its modest size. From mid-spring through mid-summer, masses of lilac-blue flowers dance across a tiny backdrop of fresh green foliage. While people love this easy-to grow perennial, deer and rabbits do not, making this plant a reliable, long-blooming performer for critter-challenged landscapes. It has an attractive cottage-garden look when grown in a border or as a groundcover, and is equally charming tumbling out of rockeries and containers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Committee', '2007', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, 'groundcover sm. collection', '2009', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
