(401, NULL, NULL, 'Colchicum', NULL, NULL, 'autumnale', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4 to 9', 'bulb', 'deciduous', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'spring', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4', '9', 'Colchicum autumnale is a vigorous, cormous perennial, bearing erect, linear, lanced-shaped leaves to 14 inches which go dormant in early summer. In autumn it produces 1 to 6 goblet-shaped, lavender-pink flowers which are 4 to 6 inches tall.', 'Autumn crocus grows best in well-drained soil with full sun. When it blooms it has no leaves, so planting it next to a smaller groundcover will help to support the flower. In winter the strappy green leaves appear and can be cut back in early summer once they start to yellow. ', 'Colchicum autumnale is a stand out in the garden because of its surprise factor. This tough bulb has broad strappy shiny foliage in late winter through spring but then goes dormant for the summer. However, come September - surprise! Its large crocus-shaped lavender-pink blooms burst from the ground to provide a splash of brilliance in late summer and early fall. Colchicum autumnale is very drought tolerant and increases to a full patch quickly. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Graves', '2005', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, 'create sm. collection with cultivars', '2008', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
(402, NULL, NULL, 'Colchicum', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Waterlily', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4 to 9', 'bulb', 'deciduous', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'fall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.4', '4', '9', 'Colchicum ''Waterlily'' is a vigorous, cormous perennial, bearing erect, linear lanced-shaped leaves 7 to 10 inches which go dormant in early summer. In autumn it produces 1 to 6 goblet-shaped, double lavender-pink flowers which are 4 to 5 inches tall.', 'Autumn crocus grows best in well-drained soil with full sun. When it blooms it has no leaves, so planting it next to a smaller groundcover will help to support the flower. In winter the strappy green leaves appear and can be cut back in early summer once they start to yellow. ', 'In September pink and creamy white buds burst from the ground and quickly open to large fully double lavender- pink blooms. The vibrant flowers are a welcome site at this time of the year and really do look like waterlily blooms! Bright green strappy shiny foliage will appear in late winter through early summer, after which the bulb will go dormant till late summer. This beautiful bulb is completely drought tolerant. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Graves', '2005', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, NULL, '2008', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
