(419, NULL, NULL, 'Cornus', NULL, NULL, 'mas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'tree', 'deciduous', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'spring', NULL, NULL, 'autumn color', NULL, '10', '10', '15', '15', '5', '8', 'Cornus mas is a deciduous small tree that often produces multiple trunks and an oval-shaped crown. This moderate grower reaches 10 feet high and wide in ten years, maturing at about 15 feet high and wide. It can easily be trained as a single- trunk tree. ', 'Plant this slow growing tree in a moist to well-drained soil with full sun to light or open shade.  It can be adaptable to sandy soils or clay and is quite drought tolerant once established. ', 'Round, fat flower buds burst into bright yellow clusters of bloom in the middle of winter brightening the gray rainy days. This lovely small tree is easy to grow and tolerates a wide range of conditions and is quite drought tolerant once established. In late summer edible, red fruit hangs from the branches but are usually too tart to eat fresh. On older trees the crooked twisted trunks will flake and peel in tan, gray and brown patches. Autumn leaf color is a rich, purple-red.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Hartlage', '2002', 'Trees - Conifers', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, NULL, '2002', 'small-tree ', NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
