(821, NULL, NULL, 'Hydrangea', NULL, NULL, 'quercifolia', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Snow Queen', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', NULL, '', '', 'shrub', 'deciduous', '', '', '', '', '', 'summer', '', '', 'autumn color ', '', '', '', '', '', '5', '8', 'Hydrangea quercifolia ''Snow Queen'' grows to 4 to 5 feet and spreads 5 to 6 feet in 10 years. ', 'Plant Hydrangea quercifolia ''Snow Queen'' in full sun or part shade in fertile, humus-rich, well-drained soil. The autumn color is best in full sun.', 'Oakleaf hydrangea adds contrast and substance to the garden due to its large, oak-shaped leaves and dramatic flower heads. The flower heads are pyramidal in shape and appear in midsummer. They are comprised of many small white flowers that fade to rose-pink. This mound-forming shrub''s leaves turn deep plum purple for a long period in autumn. The species is native to the southeastern United States. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Gossler, Rutherford, McCulloch', '2001', 'Shrubs - Vines', '', '', '', 'GPP', '', '', '2001', '', '', 'Yes', '');
