(1530, NULL, NULL, 'Syringa', NULL, NULL, 'pubescens', 'ssp.', 'patula', NULL, 'Miss Kim', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', NULL, '', '', 'shrub', 'deciduous', 'compact', 'full sun', 'regular to occasional watering', 'fertile soil to those that are less so', '', 'spring', '', 'yes', 'autumn color', '', '6', '5', '', '', '4', '8', '', 'Dwarf Korean lilac is very resilient and easy to grow, performing well in poor soil and somewhat dry conditions. Established plants only need watering in extended dry spells. Dwarf Korean lilac flowers best and has the richest fall color in full sun. Leaves break down quickly once they fall, eliminating the need for raking. Prune only to remove weak or dead branches. Old plants can be rejuvenated if necessary by  removing older stems at ground level.', 'Syringa pubescens subsp. patula ''Miss Kim'' is one of the most disease-resistant lilacs for the Pacific Northwest. Appearing in mid-to late May, pale pink-purple flowers carry a sweet but not overpowering fragrance. In autumn the small leaves turn yellow with a purple blush. This useful lilac is a slow grower that forms a compact, somewhat rounded shrub. The overall impression created by its small leaves and finely branched structure is neat and delicate-perfect for the small-space garden or for complementing small conifers or broadleaf evergreens with medium-sized leaves. Use it in the perennial border to add structure to a bed. If you want a lilac but don''t have a great deal of room, this is for you!', '', NULL, NULL, 'Blue', '2003', 'Shrubs - Vines', '', '', '', 'GPP', '', '', '2004', '', '', 'Yes', ''),
