(319, 'Rhamnaceae', 'Buckthorn', 'Ceanothus', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Victoria', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'shrub', 'evergreen', 'upright', 'full sun', 'average, drought tolerant when established', 'well drained', 'Yes', 'spring-summer', NULL, NULL, 'year around foliage, late spring flowers', NULL, '4', '6', '10-12', '9', '7', '9', 'This dense, rounded, evergreen shrub grows to about 4 feet wide and 6 feet wide in ten years. Eventually it can reach 9 feet high and 10 to 12 feet wide. ', 'Ceanothus ‘Victoria’ requires full sun and well-drained soil. It doesn’t mind salt-laden sea air, so is often planted in seaside gardens. It is drought tolerant once established but should be planted in locations with protection from wind in colder zone 7 gardens. Light pruning in early summer will create a dense plant. ', 'This selection is simply the hardiest of the California lilacs available and the most reliable for our climate. The brilliant bright indigo blue flowers are an absolute show stopper in the spring and look great against the shiny and dark evergreen foliage. This tough shrub is extremely drought tolerant once established and is a fast grower and will quickly fill an empty space. ‘Victoria’ was one of the best rated Ceanothus in the GPP trials. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mason, Dinsdale, Svenson, Blue', '2001', 'Shrubs - Vines', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, NULL, '2006', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL),
