(339, NULL, NULL, 'Chaerophyllum', NULL, NULL, 'hirsutum', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Roseum', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '6 to 9', 'perennial', 'deciduous', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'spring', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '2', '6', '9', 'Chaerophyllum hirsutum ''Roseum'' is an herbaceous perennial that produces ovate to heart-shaped leaflets, 5 to 10 inches long which are ferny in appearance on 24 inch spikes that are 12 inches wide. Umbels of pink flowers are borne above from late spring to mid-summer.  ', 'This lacey foliaged herbaceous perennial does best in full sun to part shade in rich well-drained to moist soils. Faded flowers can be left to spread seed or deadheaded to keep the plant looking its best. In fall cut yellowing foliage to the ground. ', 'A lovely and choice perennial for softening the garden, Chaerophyllum hirsutum ‘Roseum’ has beautiful apple-scented, ferny foliage that emerges in early spring and looks great through the growing season. Soon after the leaves sprout in the spring, pale rosy-pink flowers bloom well above the foliage. The delicate flowers have a wonderful lacey quality and are reminiscent of a soft pink Queen Anne’s lace. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Hammond, Elliott', '2004', 'Perennials - Bulbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GPP', NULL, NULL, '2008', NULL, NULL, 'Yes', NULL);
